race.comment: Good race for SUPERSET (1), who's been well held his past two but they have been in 66 grade and will relish the drop back to this sort of company. The last time he raced in 56 grade he defeated Tookay Pete, who has gone on to be a city winner since. MISS TRUSTFUL (3) finished seventh over 1500m at Bendigo at her most recent appearance on October 5, but was a winner in 62 grade the start prior. First up here and will be better over further but won her latest trial coming into this. GRAMMY'S SUNSHINE (11) was safely held when fourth last time out over 1200m at Cranbourne, beaten 5 lengths, but broke her maiden in style the start prior and draws to play a key role here. MISTY EMOTIONS (15) resumes. Given three quiet trials in readiness for this.
